@vegaforcecompany_usa Carl Gustaf at the @eliteforceairsoft booth. 
Elite Force says the VFC Carl Gustaf will be available April 2023. It will MSRP for approximately $700.00. Not sure how many shells it will come with, but it will include the optic mount (pictured on the tube). Power source is green gas contained inside a mock shell.

Probably the coolest product announced at SHOT Show is the @holosun DM-TH. This is a red dot optic with a thermal overlay. It has an 8x digital zoom and various modes such has white hot and black hot. 
It’s primary application is for hog hunting but this could be incredibly OP in airsoft. Only downside being there’s no way to protect the sensor. $1700.00 optic could get broken by a single 0.001 cent piece of plastic.

This is Japan’s first fully automatic airsoft gun. The JAC Battle Master was created by Ichiro Nagata in 1986. It’s power source is Freon silicone gas can that you screw directly into the gun (pictured). It holds 30 BB’s in a tube magazine and can fire semi-automatic and fully-automatic. Collector pieces have been sold for upwards of $1,200.00.

Check my stories everyday til June 12 for the link to comment opposing CPSC-2023-0021. 
Opposition template⬇️⬇️⬇️
I STRONGLY OPPOSE the Consumer Product Safety Commission’s proposed Direct Final Rule in Docket No. CPSC-2023-0021. 
Airsoft is an important, safe sporting activity, enjoyed by myself and thousands of responsible users and hobbyists. As written, the effect of the Commission’s proposed rule would have significant and unnecessary impact on myself and all in the air-soft industry, both from an economic standpoint and an accessibility one.  Without comment from the industry, the proposed Direct Final Rule would be inappropriate and unacceptable without changes.
Accordingly, I request the Commission withdraw the proposed direct final rule.  I appreciate and understand the Commission’s approach and request the Commission consider excepting air-soft guns from any requirement for GCCs.
Thank you for your consideration.
